    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Available is a mechanically sorted 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the high-revving S54B32 power plant. This 3.2L straight-six utilizes individual throttle bodies and Double VANOS variable valve timing to produce 333 hp with a distinct metallic rasp. Critical preventative maintenance has been prioritized: the rear subframe has been reinforced with plates, rod bearings have been replaced with treated shells, and the VANOS unit has been overhauled with uprated seals and a cryo-treated hub. Power is delivered through a 6-speed Getrag manual transmission to a factory limited-slip differential. The chassis remains taut thanks to a recent refresh of the trailing arm bushings and the installation of Bilstein B6 dampers. While the Alpine White paint and interior show honest patina from spirited use, the mechanical synchronization and drivetrain integrity are excellent, making this a turn-key enthusiast's machine.",
      "price": 33500.0,
